snippet: Rory McIlroy produced the best round of the day, a seven-under-par 65, but Bubba Watson’s 67 was enough to keep him atop the W.G.C.-Cadillac Championship leader board.
abstract: Bubba Watson takes third-round lead at the WGC-Cadillac Championship golf tournament.
lead_paragraph: Rory McIlroy produced the best round of the day, a seven-under-par 65, but Bubba Watson’s 67 was enough to keep him atop the W.G.C.-Cadillac Championship leader board.

headline.seo: McIlroy’s Third-Round 65 Leaves Him Eight Shots Behind Watson for W.G.C. Lead
headline.main: A Course So Tamed That Even Seven Under Par Is Not a Cause for Joy
headline.print_headline: A Course So Tamed That Even Seven Under Par Is Not a Cause for Joy
